@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Imperial Data Directive";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col">
            <h1 class="display-5">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
            <p class="lead text-warning">Classification: EYES ONLY / RESTRICTED ACCESS</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card shadow-sm mb-5">
        <div class="card-body p-4">
            <h3 class="text-info mb-3">Holonet Data Collection</h3>
            <p>This registry operates on an offline, local-first architecture designed to safeguard Imperial military assets and strategic production data. No data queried or cached from external Holonet archives (like SWAPI) is transmitted to third-party entities.</p>
            
            <hr class="border-secondary my-4" />

            <h3 class="text-info mb-3">Local Storage & Cleansing</h3>
            <p>All modifications, additions, or deletions made to the fleet records are executed directly on an isolated database. Should this workstation be compromised, local databases can be completely purged by running standard database drop procedures.</p>

            <hr class="border-secondary my-4" />

            <h3 class="text-info mb-3">Interstellar Regulations</h3>
            <p>By operating this terminal, you agree to safeguard all starship schematics, crew counts, and hyperdrive ratings contained within the records from unauthorized Rebel alliance access.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>